# Single Label Generation in Labelz

**Single Label Generation** is for creating one label at a time from a template.  
It’s best for:
- testing a new template design
- printing a replacement label
- small-batch handmade orders
- validating barcode/QR before bulk runs

---

## Before you start
Make sure you have:
- an Org and Workspace selected
- at least one Template created
- your label fields ready (SKU, product name, MRP, etc.)

---

## Step-by-step: Generate a single label

### Step 1 — Open the correct template
1. Go to your **Org**
2. Open the relevant **Workspace**
3. Go to **Templates**
4. Select the template you want to use

---

### Step 2 — Choose “Generate Single Label”
Inside the template, click:
- **Generate**
- or **Create Label**
- or **Single Label Generation**
(Exact button name depends on your UI, but the flow is the same.)

---

### Step 3 — Fill in label values
Enter the values for each field in the template, for example:
- SKU
- Product name
- Size / variant
- MRP
- Net qty / batch / dates (if relevant)
- Barcode/QR value (if your template uses it)

✅ Tip: Use real values from your product catalog so the output matches production reality.

---

### Step 4 — Preview the label
Before downloading/printing:
- check alignment
- check spelling/formatting
- confirm barcode/QR placement and size

---

### Step 5 — Generate and export
Generate the label and export it in the available print-ready format (commonly PDF or image).

Then:
- download
- print
- apply to product/packaging

---

## Best practices (highly recommended)

### Use single generation as a “template test”
Before bulk printing, always generate 1 label and:
- print it once
- scan the barcode/QR
- check that nothing cuts off

### Keep consistent formatting
If you’re generating many labels over time:
- standardize SKU format
- standardize MRP formatting
- standardize date formats (MFD/EXP)

---

## Troubleshooting

### “Label preview looks correct but print is misaligned”
- Check printer scaling (avoid “Fit to page”)
- Reconfirm label size settings
- Add more margins in the template design

### “Barcode/QR doesn’t scan”
- Increase code size in template design
- Ensure whitespace around code
- Print at higher quality

### “I don’t see the option to generate a single label”
- Ensure you’re inside a template
- Check if you have permission (access control may restrict generation)
- Try refreshing or logging out/in

---

## When to use Bulk Label Generation instead
Use **Bulk Label Generation** when you need:
- many labels at once (production runs)
- serialization across a batch
- faster output for large SKU lists

